text: Excellent street tacos!!  Great snack as you're walking the strip or to sit and eat a few.

Walked over here just to get the tacos because of the "good" reviews. 
Expensive ass tiny taco; asada needs salt. The only salsa that was good was the habanero one. 
Of course they ran out of lime, radishes, and cucumber. Wonder what else they're out of, that's just what I noticed. Oh and they did not have horchata. 
Won't be coming back next time I visit the strip. 
My cashier Diego was nice, it's not his fault they don't have limes for my tacos.

So happy they opened up an EXPRESS! 
Conveniently located on the strip too! People still get any better than this. 

THE most authentic street tacos ever!
Dads, bowls, tacos, so many options
Finally!!! Street tacos on the Strip!! They shave the pastor right in front of you. So bomb!! If in Vegas have to try!!
This place is amazing!! I got the pulled chicken burrito and it was wonderful!! Also, it was $9 the best worth meal in Vegas! Ana was great as well and the music keeps you rocking, Will be back!

This is probably the worst taco restaurant I have ever been to the employees can barley speak English and the meat is bland and the over charge for tacos they are only $2.00 but $1.00 for cheese on each taco and $1.00 for sour cream so for two tacos it came out to $7.58 I would not reccomend eating here!!! Now if the food was good and they had better customer service it is a prime spot
The food at this place is PHENOMENAL, tacos are bomb, salsa is bomb, Elote is fire, love everything about this place! Highly recommend, A+ in my book!
Third time I get food poisoning from this place. Gave it the benefit of the doubt but I'm now 10 000percent sure that it was their food that made me sick

Awesome tacos!   If you are wandering around the strip in Las Vegas wanting s reasonably priced and delicious quick meal stop here. The service is friendly and the food court is clean and comfortable.   The tacos are delicious.   Authentic-tasting "street tacos".   Sauces are awesome and everything tastes fresh.    Will definitely be back!

Fantastic tacos!! These are the best tacos I've had for the quality and at an affordable price point. Nothing greasy like your local Mexican restaurant. It deserves five stars for the great tortillas that hold everything together. They're just a little bit thicker and small than your average tortilla; they don't really get soggy or stale up within 5 minutes they way most do. Salsa verde and habanero salsa were really tasty and fresh. My favorite were the chicken and carne asada. The corn cob was also superb. The corn is very sweet and juicy! Great for sharing if you cut the kernels into a plate. The service was really kind as well and gave us all cups of water.

I come here a lot to pick up food for my fianc√© and there's not one thing that he doesn't like. I'm vegetarian so I stick to only a few items my favorite is the Elote!! Fresh food. Healthy ingredients! Fast service! 

I saw a review written a few days ago. Saying the tacos should state that they are street tacos. If you look at the sign outside. It says street tacos. It basically says it everywhere that has logs. But people never read anything..
This place has the best fresh food ever! I'm a vegan and I left full, satisfied, and looking forward to coming back! I ate a veggie burrito without cheese and it was amazingly delicious! Wow!
The food was so delicious and the service was great as well thank you to Rosa for suggesting the tacos !!!

Tacos were good. The guy who took our order seemed like he'd rather be smoking a Jay but overall, I would go back. I was talking to him about Yelp and we checked in, he didn't give us the free pastor taco for checking in. Bummer.

Great place for tacos at all times of the day or night.
Wide selection of meat choices and taste.
The tacos are quite small..probably all of 3 or 4 bites and it's gone.
Probably one of the best taco places I've been to in Las Vegas. An amazing menu, courteous staff and of course the food was wonderful.
Best 4 am taco ive ever had. If your hungry and want some bomb mexican food(im from san diego) check this place out.

Omg the tacos here are so bomb!!! I definitely recommended cochinita pibil! Everytime I'm in Vegas which is every other month I always have to stop here, whether you get it in the daytime or at night after a couple drinks, this place knows how to make some delicious tacos. I've also tried the carne asada tacos, the Nopal taco and the catnitas. All of them are great you can't go wrong
Well I got to say the food taste great!!!!! Reason I have it 2 stars manager was so rude, and the staff kept yelling at us to get our food

One thing for sure is that every place along the Strip can be pricey including these hole in the wall restaurants. Get a free taco with a yelp check in. I ordered a carnitas taco, nopales taco, and street corn. My taco was okay but my girl loved her nopales taco. Keep in mind DO NOT order the street corn because it was nasty, not even close to what you get from an illegal street corn seller.
The food was under the average, it's took them 20 minutes to give us the two tacos that we ordere.

I travel all over the country for work,  I'm from Chicago and it's really hard to find a place as good as here, the cook knows the taco game, the real way to make authentic tacos, hood customer service it's a plus, great flavors and fresh ingredients! 
Thanks for the good tacos on my vacation.

Glad we found this very very reasonable place to eat at late night in Vegas.  of course,no one sleeps in Vegas with everything opens 24/7, and the staff are friendly.  Ordered the special of 15 tacos for $30 with a variety of chicken, pork, steak, and beef head (not daring to try the beef head).  Meat on the chicken was mile finely shredded, lightly salted.  Simple and delicate.  Braised pork has a saucy tender flavor with a touch of freshly citrus note, not bad.  The beef is a bit dried, but it is nicely grilled, needs something like cilantro or pickled veggie to off set the beef.   Nothing can beat the price.

this has got to be the best street taco spot.. walking on the strip hungry af.. this reminded me of cali taco... pastor was amazing.. my buddies asada was great. you cant go wrong with el dorado.. customer service is prime as well

Had a very spontaneous snack with my brother in law. Tacos were excellent! We both had one al pastor tacos each. 

Tortilla - 100% yellow corn tortilla. Good in size and fresh. Double layered

Al pastor meat - Fresh! Delicious in flavor. Savoy. Soft and tender. 

Cilantro, onions, pineapple - good portion on all. Pineapple was diced same as the onion. 

Salsas - avocado salsa and red salsa. Both were really good! Ask for extra avocado sauce. Delicious. 

Open 24/7. It's $3 a taco. There's a special offer of 15 tacos for $30. $2 a taco ain't bad! 
Check in to unlock the free al pastor taco!

This place was right across the street from where I stayed. I was looking for a cheaper option to eat on my last night and I recall seeing this place when I got donuts in this area earlier. They had a free taco giveway if you did the Yelp check in as one of their offers. I used it on top of buying 4 more tacos. Some mix ups here... walking in no one was at the register. I was the only one here. The cook came out and acknowledged me then yelled at the cashier to come out. She intially thought I wanted just the free taco and rang me up. I had to tell her I wanted 4 more tacos with it. Both of them looked like they were still really young so maybe that had something to do with the mix ups. The food itself was alright (there's better Mexican street tacos in my hometown of San Diego). They have a banner claiming it's a Yelp top 100 eatery.  Most of their business probably comes from late night eaters as they are open 24 hours. My tab was around $12 pre tip for 4 street tacos plus one free taco from the Yelp check in offer. The one thing I thought was off putting was a side of guac was $4. Pretty steep. That cost more then the street tacos individually.
I'm had the carnita, pollo and carne asada tacos. These were great and reminded me of my last visit to Mexico. Can't wait to come back for more!

I ordered from them with Uber eats and they got my order completely wrong and also forgot my elotes. They refused to refund my order or even apologize for getting my order wrong the food was also cold.

Came here because it had great reviews and I haven't been to Mexico in a while and so finding a good street taco can be very hard. 
When we arrived they were cleaning the counters and stove so the cashier attended us. She shouted out order to the guy who had been cleaning and wiping stuff down.. I assumed he was going to change his gloves since they were clearly dirty but no that didn't happen..now I get that this may happen at other restaurants and I just don't see it cause it's in the kitchen but if you're cooking right in my face then I should be able to look at what your doing and be satisfied with the quality of my food and it's preparation. My husband is a "fire kills everything" guy and so he proceeded to eat 3 of the tacos. Long story short - either fire doesn't kill everything or the they just weren't prepared correctly because he ended up getting heartburn and indigestion. We had also gotten a Nopal taco which I tasted since it was prepped by someone else but it was still very greasy. 

Overall not a good experience and I hope that they get better about cleanliness and food contamination.

Al Pastor was delicious and right on the money! PinkBox is inside as well. A delicious donuts company. The music is great, friendly wait staff and the taco was awesome! I wash I was hungrier this AM lol
Great food! Very slow service! Ordered the carne Asada burrito and it was delicious! The meat was tender and seasoned! Prices are a bit ridiculous! Tacos are pretty good! Street corn was okay!

From the minute I walked in, I could smell the delicious food. After we ordered, the chef, Paco, walked around greeted everyone and answered any questions we had. Bonus points all their food is organic and GMO free. I had the burrito which was HUGE! The carne Asada was perfectly
Marinated and cooked to perfection. There's a reason why this was ranked in the top 30 restaurants nationally. Highly recommend this over just about any other restaurant I have ever been. Insider secret, the churros are better than the ones at Disneyland!

Oh my lord! The pull pork tacos was spectacular! The funny thing is I was still full because just had my dinner an hour ago. But This drunk guy talked me into it.  So yes... pull pork tacos is the bomb dot com! I licked my plates clean- no shame what-so-ever! So clean, so fresh! Nomination! Ate it so fast that I forgot to take a picture *facepalm*

But yes pull pork tacos is full of flavor. For less than $3... you get a party in your mouth!
The pollo chicken burrito was awesome. One of the best burritos I've ever had. I will definitely go back.

Food was good!  Salsa was awesome but the customer service and wait was terrible!  Our food took 20 minutes to arrive and after the food arrived, they forgot one of my tacos.  Chairs were dirty and no one was bussing the tables.  Not to mention the long line and the confusion amongst the waiters and cooks as to who placed what order.  Food was wondering from outside to inside and the food servers were lost...

Price for the tacos was also just a bit high but the tacos were good...

Stopped by here for some street tacos. This is located in a little food court. Don't let that stop you from ordering. We tried about 6 different tacos. Each meat was delirious. Pleasant of salsa varieties to choose from. Definitely worth trying.

Needs better management. Only waited 30 minutes. Cold Tacos.
Bathroom very dirty. Don't remove my post. This is the truth. Other people have put bad reviews and you guys take them down. 
How long has that meat been setting out. Over night but you guys still sell it. How long has the beans been setting there more then 2 hours. The health department should close this place down.
You guys are totally gross you guys never wear gloves. And what about the hair in my rice Bowl. The guacamole taste like avocado all of your food has no taste. I nominate this place as the worses Mexican place to eat in Vegas!!!!!!!

My mouth is watering just thinking about this place! It is soooo good! The tacos are fresh and yummy! The Mexican Street corn is so good it it SINFUL! The salsas truly had me fall in love and I went back for seconds and thirds! Did I mention that the place is super clean and the staff is super friendly? I can't wait to be back!!

Want something relatively quick and delicious while on the strip? Check this place out. Every place on the weekend is over crowded and hectic in Vegas. This little gem hides in a mini food court. Ordered the Carne asada burrito and it was bomb. The side of refried beans and tortilla chips were lack luster but the burrito was great! The salsa bar was a nice touch. Was really not expecting much from this place. But always love a good surprise.

RECOMMENDED FOR:
~anyone hungry
~those needing food in the middle of the night
~delicious tacos

I was so excited to find the new Boulevard Food Court.  Its literally less than a ten minute walk from my room at the Grand Chateau until I'm ordering!  They are open 24 hours!  This is fantastic.

Inside you will find a pizza place, a donut shop and El Dorado Express.   The food court has indoor and outdoor covered seating.  There are restrooms there, accessible with a code that comes on your receipt.

El Dorado Express is an offshoot of El Dorado Cantina which is one of the best Mexican restaurants in Las Vegas in my opinion so I was excited to try it out.  They have a good sized menu, but its about the tacos!  Yelp check ins get you a free taco and on Tuesdays street tacos are $2 each.

I had one carnitas taco, one cochinita taco and one al pastor taco.  They were all yummy and I cannot pick between the al pastor and the cochinita for my favorite... they both had delicious elements.  

Overall, I see myself coming here pretty much every time I'm in Vegas.  I highly recommend it as an affordable place to eat a quick meal.  Seriously, the tacos.
One of the best steak street tacos I've ever had at a very good price for the strip. So glad I tried this place.

Had some carne Assad tacos and al pastor tacos. The service was really fast and the tacos were spot on. The salsa was also really good. I wish they had a spicier option for the salsa but overall satisfied with everything.
So good!!  The carne asada was number 1 and the el pastor taco a close second.  Chicken burrito is good too but I don't think you can go wrong with anything you order here.

Not sure why they have express in their name. It took over 25 minutes to get my 2 carne Assad's tacos. They were completely plain; no onion; cilantro, etc. they're open 24 hours and they tasted pretty good. Work on the express part and this might be a great place. For now 3 stars.
Absolutely delicious! I ordered tacos Al pastor, & they were so good! The food is reasonably price for the strip.
This place has really good al pastor but the amount of meat to cost ratio and slightly soggy corn tortia brought down 1 star for me.

The most delicious tacos in Vegas! 2 dollar Tuesday! Any day! If you're on the strip and you don't want to be ripped off, come here and enjoy authentic Mexican food! Come and see Rosa she is a wonderful server, very attentive and helpful!
Yummy tacos but al pastor taco had a lot of fat but they were very good, corn on the cob was pricey 4.50 just mayo, cheese and a sprinkle of Chile
Carne Asada tacos are sooooooooo good! Definitely going to crave them all the time, and definitely a restaurant to remember.

A very accesible place to get to when walking on the strip located at the Boulevard Food Court. Very clean and friendly staff. The food is fresh and made in front of you. I had the tacos al pastor and cabeza, very filling and great price. 
The soft tortillas made these tacos stand out from the rest, they were delicious. The best place to eat Mexican food is at El Dorado cantina so I've been looking forward to try their express taco location. You could tell it had Chef Paco's touch, full of flavor.

Was here today and honestly it's the worse place  i have been guy cooking has a really bad attitude towards customers. Order about 95 -100 dollars in tacos and after order 3 corn on the cob.  Ask guy to cut it his attitude against me was unacceptable. Owner should be more consistent in being their he might get ur customers away. By the way I only put one star cuz couldn't put zero.
Great Al Pastor taco! Don't forget to check in and get your free taco! Good food, very reasonably priced and super clean eatery!

Best Vegas tacos EVER!!!! 
Not expensive and a good location when your in between meals on the strip.....
I like to start by giving each place five stars. Every time I find something wrong I take a star off. I couldn't find anything wrong with this place. Food was good and it came out quickly.

Customer service is awesome. Very pleased with the price and taste of food. We will be returning on our next trip. The corn on the cob was delicious, so soft and perfect temperature. We are the pastor meat and carne asada both great taste.
You know what's more lit than the el pastor fire? Their nopal tacos! Such great lighting in this place,  super clean too and the food did not take long to make and was more than filling!

Burrito just rice and beans, where is the protein? Almost anything.
I've ordered a guacamole and chips, they brought me mashed avocado.
The worst Mexican restaurant that I've been.

Bought 6 carne asada tacos and 1 hot cheeto covered street corn. Food is not Authentic meat had no type of seasoning. Corn was plain no flavor what so ever, place is clean  prices are like 2.95 per taco drinks $3 corn $4. Would not come here again Taco Bell steak tacos are way better and cheaper!

I don't know how this place has been getting four stars. Their meat is absolute garbage. The carnitas was pure fat and was the most disgusting thing I have eaten on my trip. The taco size is extremely small and not worth even a buck a taco. I did enjoy spiking my gross food into their garbage!!!!!!

My favorite place to get an authentic elote! Their tacos are so flavorful, and I love the convenience of this location if I'm nearby at Topgolf or the Showcase movie theater. If you're wanting authentic Mexican food quickly, come check out this location. Thanks Ana for your great service!

OMG!!!! I love love love fresh pineapple water!!!! No doubt thee best I've had in a very long time! Went looking for a quick lunch and wandered in here to check out the menu.. I was pleasantly surprised when I saw the asada fries and pastor street tacos. Now they're definitely not in the same league as Roberto's BUT I must admit for 6.00 bucks the fries were fantastic! The tacos were pretty small but had tons of flavor especially with the fresh mango on top and a little pricey, but it's the strip right.. service was friendly and fairly fast. I'll definitely be going back to get that delicious water!!!!!!!!!
The food is amazing, the tacos are Amazing! I recommend the "Carne Asada" tacos. The tortillas they use are a great. This place is a must try while in Vegas.

Not too bad, we were looking for a quick and not too filling breakfast. We came here and got a donut at pink box (cookies and cream was delicious) which is in the same building and then grabbed a carnitas and carne asada Taco to share. Portions were very small for $3.00 a Taco, but you are on the strip so expect nothing more than overpriced food. So nice to get something other than eggs and pancakes for a quick breakfast. Manager waited on us and was very friendly and helpful in translating the choices.

This has to be the worst Mexican Food I ever ate. Their meat is bland, their rice is bland, even their tortilla chips are bland. How can you have bland chips and salsa? I asked for hot sauce and they didn't even give me that as well. There are so much better options then to eat at this place. HOWEVER if you're like me and want to throw away money, then by my guest,  throw your money away in this establishment. 

I would HIGHLY recommend anywhere else besides this place. If you find a pizza on the floor, it would still be better than the food they serve here!

Worst place ever, there was no people and they took over 35 mins to bring us our food out. When it finally came out it was all cold, and there was absolutely no flavor in the food. We asked our server for our drinks and she said "I'll bring in a min". We waited 5 mins more, finally decided to get up ask for it ourself. I do not recommend this place at all.
Delicioso! Great service and the tacos are amazing! They have taco tuesday which is $2 each, great price for the product. Totally recomended

This is definitely a "hole in the wall" type Mexican restaurant.  Located on the strip between the MGM and Polo Casino.  Surprising great tasting and fresh ingredients.  Try the carne asada taco!  Cubes of soft, seasoned steak on 2 flour disks.  Great salsa bar.

Taco Tuesdays:  Almost all tacos are $2!

Always open, this is great hangover food!
This is one of my favorite spots on the strip.  Always taste good and the service is great, ask for Bethanie.  Veggie burrito is bomb!
Haven't had a carne asada burrito this good since I lived in the Mission District of San Francisco. Delicioso.

Open 24 hours show up and they don't have enough food. "Maybe enough for 3 carne asada burritos because we are cleaning" asked if they could make us anything since we walked 20 minutes and the guy said no. That's all we have.
It was good. The tacos could of been a little bit bigger or a little less expensive... The service was cool and the restaurant was clean. I'd come back for a second visit.

The one start is because it was nice and clean. 

We went to this place because it said it was yelps top 100 places in the US. And it's on the strip. Couldn't be that bad right 

I personally don't think it's hat easy to mess up Mexican food but this restaurant def managed. 

We ordered a chicken burrito and nachos. 

It has to have been the blandest Mexican food i have ever had. 

Boiled white rice and boiled shredded chicken. There was no flavor whatsoever. We had to drench our food in all the salsa possible to attempt to finish our meal. 
Super super disappointed.

I wouldn't call it one of the top 100 places to eat as their advertising does.
Food was ok
Nothing special 
Had carne asada burrito.  Mostly was rice. 
$10.95 for a burrito is a bit much when it was dry no sauces mostly rice little meat, little beans .
And a glass of soda at $4.00 was way over priced . Even the neighbor location ( there are several food places in the court) was only $1.99

Probably will never go back.

Solid tacos on the Las Vegas strip. It's surprisingly hard to find authentic Mexican food in the resort district. This is probably as close as you're likely to find. Their carnitas is my favorite. 

Tacos as simple street style, two 3-4" soft corn tortillas with a large helping of meat on each. There's a salsa bar for toppings. I recommend the salsa verde, it's not the best in the world but it compliments the pork quite well. Only complaint about the tacos is the price. At $2.95 each it's hard to get full without spending a lot.

The quesadillas are good too. They use real cheese and dry cook them (no oil or, God so help me, butter) on the outside like you see at some places. Served with a side of chips, these are the best deal in my opinion at $4-8 each.

Burritos were the least good. Not bad, just not amazing either and at $8-10 not a great deal either. The meats are the same as the other items, it's the rice and beans that lets this dish down. They're both bland. Stick the other items or find yourself a salt shaker and grab some salsa.

I'll be back on my next trip to Vegas.

We came into this place around 2am on a Saturday (technically Sunday lol) after a night out. I was just delighted to see that we weren't eating at a janky place cause that's usually what is open at this time. The restaurant was very well kept with empty tables clean and the floor swept. Ali, the night manager, was very friendly and upbeat which helped boosted my spirits . 

I got two al pastor tacos, one carne asada, and one cabeza. The al pastor is delicious. It comes with pineapple bits and a creamy green sauce on top. It reminds me a lot of the Taco Stand al pastor in SD. The carne asada and the cabeza were both well cooked and tender but they were bland in my opinion. I put some green onions and their tomatillo sauce and it was good! 

All in all, great place for some tacos in the middle of the night!

This restaurant is in between Planet Hollywood and MGM in one of the shopping complexes on Las Vegas Blvd. We were strolling between the two aforementioned casinos, and noticed this restaurant with very good rating. Mrs. said why not and got a Quesadilla for Ian and a burrito for herself. (Total for both was $15.16) I had already eaten my fair share earlier in the day so I was just there for company. There is seating inside as well as outside and they share space with another business (Pizza and Donut maybe?). 

The Burrito was utterly delicious.
Ian's quesadilla was on the cheesy side, but there is no denying the taste present in the Tortilla and the way it was cooked. 

If you are craving for some Mexican food to satisfy your late night hunger, definitely drop by here. They are open 24 Hour.

After seeing a show, we wanted tacos.  Of course, I went to Yelp and found El Dorado Express.  Located in the Boulevard Food Court, they share the area with a few other fast food joints, such as a coffee shop and pizza.  So, it's nice that there are other options , but there isn't much seating inside.  There is a pretty large patio but who wants to sit outside in the middle of summer?  

After seeing the high reviews on Yelp, we headed on over.  Unfortunately, they did not live up to those reviews.  I'm guessing that those high reviews were written after a few too many drinks when anything tastes great.  First off, we were told they were running about 15 minutes behind so we'd have to wait for our food.  Okay.  So, we ordered some chips and salsa, hoping to enjoy those while we waited, but nope.  They came out with our tacos.  How hard is it to reach behind you, grab us some chips and salsa, and send us on our way? When we finally did receive our food, I was surprised to see how small the tacos were.  It was fine because they were only $2.50 each, but the menu should specify that they are street tacos.  At this point, I was glad that we ordered the chips and salsa because there was no way two street tacos were going to fill us up and I wasn't willing to wait another 15 minutes.  The tacos also weren't anything special.  They were just okay.  I ordered one al pastor and one carne asada while the hubs ordered one pork and one chicken.  They were all kind of plain and lacked much flavor.  Needless to say, I was pretty disappointed and wouldn't stop in here again.

This is probably my last trip here. We stopped because yelp said they are one of the best restaurants in the US. Authentic Mexican cuisine. My wife (Mexican) got some tacos and I got the carne asada burrito. My wife said that the tacos where ok that she had better. Now my burrito when I got it it was cut in half and I can see inside it. It was full of white rice. Only had a little meat. I payed $10 the a rice burrito lol. Come on when you think of authentic Mexican food you think of a burrito full of meat, beans, tomatoes, cilantro, avocados and flavors! If I wanted a sushi burrito I would of gone to a sushi bar. If you want good tacos go to DJ tacos or somewhere else down the street. You will thank me.

Quick, easy, and authentic food. The meat is grilled and that's what gives it an amazing flavor. The tortillas are cooked  in a little oil and the cheese just melts so right. We got an order of carne asada tacos and a quesadilla. They have some fresh tasting salsas too that again are real salsas and not Pace. Along with salsas they have grilled, pickled jalapenos and veggies plus some diced onion and Cilantro to top off the tacos. Also limes, cucumbers and rabanos in their salsa bar. Definitely wanted to keep eating here. The prices are a little up there though but really good food.

While walking up and down the strip, we fell upon this "express" version of the El Dorado Cantina restaurant in Vegas. Perused the menu and had to try their street tacos that they were famous for when the first opened and were $1 for Happy Hour. Well, they are now $2.95 , but they do have a yelp check in for one free taco , so take advantage of that. Had a delicious Al Pastor taco which was delicious as well as one of their quesadillas which was pretty average. I think their Taco's are the clear standout here. Nice that the venue is 24 hrs, although that maybe common on the strip.

New and good!  The service is great and the food is awesome.  *this is a sober review! . Food is fast and delicious!  I'll definitely be back!  Had the al pastor tacos.  Not as good as in places like Guadalajara, but it works for Vegas!  It's a new food court so hopefully they'll keep it up.  There are wings, dogs and coffee in the food court as well. Open 24 hours!

Walking along the Vegas strip is this awesome spot!  If it wasn't for the sign outside, "Yelpers give us great reviews,"  I probably wouldn't have stopped by here.  The sign just made me look up this restaurant and to my finding, the sign was correct!  

We had to find out ourselves how great this place is.  The entire restaurant was completely empty for the beginning of the dinner hour.   Our attendant made a recommendation and so we ordered two of the Al Pastor Tacos ($2.95) and a veggie burrito ($8).  To our surprise, their food was extremely fresh and authentic!  Basically reminded me of Mexico and we greatly loved it!  Their sauces and pico de Gallo is amazing also.  There's a little salsa buffet area to select from and so don't shy away from it, especially if you enjoy sauce and spices.

A definite hole in the wall; really reminded of my favorite taco food truck but in an open restaurant with several seating and tables.  Did I mention right on the Vegas strip and open 24 hours a day!  Crazy right?  Well, with so many bars and party people around this open restaurant they keep security around.  The restaurant was clean and they kept their bathrooms really clean also.  For some authentic tacos and at a low price you can't go wrong but to stop in and try for yourself.  Plus, for every Yelp Checkin, you receive a free taco!  Check it out!
I rarely give 5 stars, but this place is bomb. Nice little hike in the wall with great food, and reasonable prices.
Waited over twenty minutes for four small steak tacos with barely anyone in the place. Lame

I hardly give five stars. Actually hardly give any good reviews unless everything is perfect. I have worked in restaurant industry, my girlfriend is manager for several restaurants. By far this is the most perfect casual dining restaurant we have seen. Super clean, simple decor, good uniforms, friendly cashier, fast kitchen. Perfect tasting food. I live in Chicago where there is a Taco place in every corner. However, this is probably the best Mexican food i have ever had. 

Plus when it got busy the manager stopped working on his lap-top jumped in the kitchen helping. He was very supportive and friendly to his employees. That is what makes the difference between a boss and a leader.

Whenever i go to Vegas, I will include El Dorado Express in my to visit places.

If your looking for a 24/7 quick bite to eat then probably might hit your needs. Food wise (Taco) in this case was okay at best. The flavor of the Pastor wasn't flavorful and different then what I have normally had of other Pastor taco.

The food was AMAZING!!! We tried every taco, a burrito, and a quesadilla (very hungry group). Everything was so good and the service was stellar. The prices are crazy low for how much you get, and how GREAT the food was!!

Mhhhmm! This was place was amazing. My husband and I love mexican food. And if we see tacos, we want them right away. We came here for our last day in Vegas and the food was amazing. I ordered the carne asada tacos and my husband got the burrito. Everything was cooked fresh, even the chips and salsa! Everything was great. The service was great, the food was great and their location is very convenient on the strip! After days of partying, this was exactly what we needed!

So 2am just got back from the club and the lady at the cash register thinks I am to tipsy because I just ordered and instead of giving me correct change she hand me back olny the cents don't come here after hours complete rip off!!! Beware!!!! 100% Beware!!!!!
This was the best meal we had in Vegas. The food is reasonably priced compared to most places on the Strip. The roasted corn was delicious!

By far the worst SERVICE up and down the strip. Food definitely not worth the service there. We work on the strip tried this place multiple times and always heard from customers it was horrible but had to try it out ourselves. THE WORST EMPLOYEES I've had different people different times and it doesn't change. Simple request or changes to a very basic menu and they make a big deal about it laughing and talking Spanish right in front of you. There are so many better spots to eat right around this place I would not recommend this place to anyone.

This place is open 24 hours right on the Las Vegas Strip. I initially ordered one carne asado taco and one cochinitas tacos then got a free taco al pastor for Yelp check-in. Yaaayyy!! The meats were very tender and well seasoned.

This El Dorado Express is a God send. I discovered the full restaurant a few years back and make it a point to visit every time I come to Vegas. So you can imagine my surprise and excitement level when I arrived memorial weekend to see there was an El Dorado on the strip. That was my first stop for food when I got to Vegas that night. I was in heaven at 1 am eating my carnitas burrito and they prices were super cheap!
I had heard about this place and it did not disappoint!! The food was amazing and the service was outstanding! It came out hot and delish

This place is open 24/7 on the strip so make sure you stop by this place if you have some late night taco cravings. I love the convenience of this location (since it's closer than the original place).

Prices are $2.95 for each taco including al pastor, cochinita, carne asada, pollo, and others. I liked the al pastor, the pineapple chunks were a nice addition and the sauce on top added a little kick. The carne asada didn't come with any toppings but there are sauces for you to put on. The pollo was shredded chicken which was different from what I expected. It was a little dry but the salsa on top helped the flavor.

They have great service and the food came out pretty quickly. This place is very clean too which I think is rare for the typical 24/7 places.

I was very disappointed because these tacos are meant for babies!!!! Seriously they are way too small and I am still hungry! I gave three stars because they were actually really good, just too overpriced and not advertised as street tacos. Good place for an appetizer or snack, NOT a meal.
Pork and beef tacos were good. But not recommend the corn!!!  It tasted really weird. Price is reasonable.

Never get burritos filled with mostly beens and rice...
Go for tacos kind of expensive but much better
Trato muy amable y limpio el lugar y la comida deliciosa ideal para benir con la familia y amigos

This is going to be my go to from now on. The staff was amazing! Jose was fast and friendly on the grill. Diego was very energetic and efficient on the register. The General manager Mike Lee came out to make sure we enjoyed our food. I will bring all my friends here

Pricey (6 tacos and 2 drinks for $25) but the tacos were delicious and flavorful. We unfortunately couldn't tell which was which but we're not picky. We split everything between two people and wish they had given us two plates instead of just one. Service was quick enough - we weren't in a rush. Nice location - in the same place as a pizza place and donut shop. We got donuts for dessert.

Tried this place for the first time, about 3 days ago. The tacos were pretty good, i got two pastor and one asada. The pastor was good and so was the asada. Naturally, i compared it to the pastor at Tacos El Gordo, and Tacos El Gordo pastor was better. The location is great and is right next to Fatburger, in a lil food court with a few options of different types of food. Service was excellent, and everyone was really nice. They also give you a free pastor taco for checking in on Yelp.
We were walking down the strip in search of midnight tacos and I thought this place was going to suck. I was totally skeptical but it was great, perfect. Tacos were exactly what the doctor ordered.

Any place that's open 24 hrs and claims to have the best tacos in Vegas (as rated by Yelp) will peak my interest. Add in a full Vegas day of walking and partying and I was starving for a quick bite before heading to bed. 

Tried the veggie nachos which were basically chicken nachos without chicken, but they didn't give me grief about it so that was great. They were quick and tasty. So much so that I went back the next day and had them again (I will say that had more to do with convenience than how good they were). My husband had the chicken quesadilla and a pastor taco and said both were very good.

This is a perfect Vegas late night find!

These tacos were $3 ped taco.. let that sink in. Look at how dry it is. Not flavorful. 10 bucks for the worst carne asada burrito ever. "Votes by yelp one of the best in U.S." This is a lie
.

So my review may be a little influenced due to alcohol.... lol... After drinking beer, walking up and down the strip, dancing to latin music, watching some weird street performers, I found myself standing in front of El Dorado Express... It was a hell of a treat because at 3 am and many beers, the only thing anyone really wants is TACOS!!! I ordered myself the Elote, 3 carne asada and 2 al pastor... 

After receiving my tacos I found this salsa bar which had so many options. I went straight to the HOT. The Elote itself was one of the best ive ever had, it did need a tad bit of salt but other then that it was perfect. The tacos so amazing... I wish I had room or else I would have ordered like 10 more... The meat was juicy and tasted well seasoned. I would recommend this place to anyone... IF you want to enjoy it as much as myself do what I did... Drink all day and night and stumble in at 3am... You wont be disappointed.

The sign outside lured us in.  Line everything else in Vegas.....a gimmick.  It CLEARLY advertises 15 tacos for $30.  So....We go in and they say, "Oh that is only for Wednesday night's and Friday nights".  Does the sign say that?  NO.  I do have to admit that the tacos were excellent however not at the price advertised outside the place.
Good carne asada tacos. Don't get the "combo" unless you want a soda. They give you a small scoop of beans and 5 chips. Just get the tacos by itself.

I'm not impressed at all. For $9 I got 2 super tiny street tacos, a small paper tray of stale tortilla chips, cup of water, and a 25 minute wait 

Tacos were just ok. Meat was not as tender as I hoped, but it was edible. The salsa station was messy and not very appealing. Don't think I will be returning.
I fucking love this place . Open 24 hr . Great for when you're drunk . The nachos are super delicious
